root: ^There’s a group of small animals called pigeons hopping around. I see them everywhere in this city. Supposedly, these pigeons are flighted birds, but I think they look too fat and juicy to fly very long. I rarely see them fly away.

^Maybe that’s because the humans don’t really try to catch them. Back home, the juveniles would often try to pounce on similar creatures for a quick snack, but I haven’t seen a single human do the same. Maybe they can’t digest the pigeons?
